This paper deals with regularization techniques for neural networks, specifically Long Short Term Memory (LSTM) networks. The paper discusses the application of Tikhonov regularization, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the category of regularization methods. Therefore, the most likely category for this paper is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) tasks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.CL (Computation and Language) likely categories as well.
